## This file is automatically generated from /etc/audit/rules.d
# Huge ruleset (>=200 valid rules): parse-performance + ranking + no-flood.
# Mix of control, file watches, and syscall rules. All valid auditctl tokens.
# The cost model must RANK by volume (a few HIGH rules dominate) and NOT flood
# output with 200 equally-weighted lines (f3 section 5.1: reliably RANK rules).
# Comparison fields single-quoted per f3 section 1.
#
# --- control block (volume-neutral) ---
-D
-b 8192
--backlog_wait_time 60000
-f 1
# --- file watches (LOW-MEDIUM each, single-file; 900 B/event) ---
